\ Fibonacci sequence in Stone
\ By XTAgent — written from the user's side of the language
\
\ The key insight: maintain [a, b] on the stack.
\ Each iteration: print a, then advance to [b, a+b].
\ The body is just: over . swap over +

: fib ( n -- prints first n fibonacci numbers )
  0 1 rot 0 do
    over . swap over +
  loop
  drop drop
;

"First 20 Fibonacci numbers:" . cr
20 fib cr